OL,3,CSunderland striker opens up about
OL,4,Calcohol addiction
OL,6,F"Everything was just failing and
OL,7,Ffalling apart. It was obvious I had a
OL,8,Fproblem with alcohol for a good few
OL,9,Fyears.
OL,11,F"I decided at the end of July that it
OL,12,Fwas too much. I couldn't live the way
OL,13,FI was living. It was killing people
OL,14,Faround me to be honest, my family and
OL,15,Ffriends.
OL,17,F"I spent a month there in the summer
OL,18,Fand said to my agent I don't want you
OL,19,Fcontacting any clubs."
